MVC Exercise :
1. User Login/Register → Using ASP.NET Core Identity (or custom auth)
2. Dashboard → Show combine data grid. 
3. Error Page → Custom error messages
4. Simple CRUD with Multiple Tables	→ At least have 1 independent tables
5. Complex CRUD with Relationships → One-to-Many, Many-to-Many

Must have :						
1. Routing
2. Advanced Model Binding
3. Dependency Injection & Services
4. Filters & Middleware
5. Authentication & Authorization
6. State Management
7. Error Handling & Logging
8. Security
9. Performance & Optimization
